@carmstrong so, interestingly, the [directions you referenced](http://docs.deis.io/en/latest/managing_deis/backing_up_data/#finishing-up) don't actually work-- at least not entirely.

With the exception of user keys published under `/deis/builder/users/<username>/<key>`, all the post-save hooks are publishing to etcd _only_ when the object in question is newly created.

[Here's a good example](https://github.com/deis/deis/blob/master/controller/api/models.py#L1190-L1193):

```
def _etcd_publish_domains(**kwargs):
    domain = kwargs['instance']
    if kwargs['created']:
        _etcd_client.write('/deis/domains/{}'.format(domain), domain.app)
```

Thinking about this, I think that the bug here is probably: https://github.com/deis/deis/blob/101bbba3788043e64545a2c67ead224c4958b048/contrib/aws/gen-json.py#L108

We never want to rewrite the `-data-dir` parameter to etcd. Inside the container, it should *always* be `/var/lib/etcd`. We only want to change which volume on the host gets bind-mounted into the container.

