I just discovered that full blown browsers like Firefox and Chrome can connect to the server with the suggested configuration, which includes the line

    ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/yourdomain.com/cert.pem;

but clients like curl and wget don't. The reasons are explained shortly in the first answer to #2026 and in detail [on the nginx site](http://nginx.org/en/docs/http/configuring_https_servers.html#chains).

TL;DR use this instead:

    ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/yourdomain.com/fullchain.pem;

